60814"},{"created_at":"2014-01-09T21:45:44Z","content":"AJ and I were friends in high school.  Even after all of the stuff he had been through, he was a great guy on the inside; which is how it should be.  He did not deserve to die the way he did.  And for the person who killed him to only lose three years of his life is a disgrace.  If I understand correctly, the individual responsible for this has a past history of drinking and driving.  If he has not learned from his past mistakes, what is three years going to teach him.  I sincerely hope the judge comes to their senses; how would they feel if it was something the knew and care about.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stacie Johnson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75658923"},{"created_at":"2014-01-09T21:32:29Z","content":"JUSTICE!!!!!!!!!!! A family lost their father,brother,uncle,son,nephew. He was doing the right thing that night. He did not get behind the wheel and drive drunk. The driver did. Riscioli needs more than 3 years!!!!!!! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"May Beam","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75656691"},{"created_at":"2014-01-09T21:08:53Z","content":"I would want justice if this were to happen to my family member. If the roles were reversed, would Abraham have gotten the same light sentencing?  I think not.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melinda Colon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62291565"},{"created_at":"2014-01-09T21:02:54Z","content":"Because people should not drink and drive and most of the time they get away with murder and go back behind the wheel and kill more people.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Aida E Lopez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6592154"},{"created_at":"2014-01-09T19:06:48Z","content":"people need to understand that there are consequences to this type of behavior and it thus should expect a tough punishment if caught!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"mildred velasquez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75636188"},{"created_at":"2014-01-09T18:59:56